The Peto method12 is a simpler version of the conditional approach. This uses the scoring method, and is virtually the same as the scoring method for the unconditional approach (the only difference in calculation is that the variance of the contributing estimate from each trial is larger by a factor of n/(n–1), where n is the total number of patients in the trial). The calculations can be done as for the inverse-variance method using Peto estimates of log odds-ratio from each study:
log OR=(oi-ei)/viSE(log OR)=√{1/vi}
